Description: bspam is an R package that contains functions to fit the speed-accuracy psychometric model for count outcome data (Potgieter, Kamata & Kara, 2017; Kara, Kamata, Potgieter & Nese, 2020), where the accuracy is modeled by a binomial count latent variable model. For example, the use of this modeling technique allows model-based calibration and scoring for oral reading fluency (ORF) assessment data.
